
<div class="pure-g">
  <div class="pure-u-3-4 modal-anchor">
    <p>
      We collect personal information in order to <span class="text-input">{{input value=model.statement.collectionReason placeholder="do something that directly relates to our business" size="45"}}</span>
    </p>

    {{#each model.statement.extraReasons as |_ index|}}
      <p>
        also, we need to
        <br />
        <span class="text-input">{{array-item-input array=model.statement.extraReasons index=index placeholder="do another thing related to our business" size="37"}}</span>
      </p>
    {{/each}}

    <p>
      <button {{action "addReason"}} class="pure-button button-black-on-white button-small">we have another reason</button>
    </p>


    <p>
      We only collect information that relates to these purposes:
    </p>


    <ul class="non-bullet-list">
      <li>
        {{radio-button value=true checked=model.statement.onlyTheseReasons id="onlyTheseReasons"}}
        <label for="onlyTheseReasons">Yes</label>
      </li>
      <li>
        {{radio-button value=false checked=model.statement.onlyTheseReasons id="moreReasons"}}
        <label for="moreReasons">No</label>
      </li>
    </ul>

    {{#if readyToMoveOn}}
        {{yield}}
    {{else}}
        <button {{action "notReady"}} class="pure-button button-blue next-step-button">move along</button>
    {{/if}}


    {{#modal-message showModal=showUnstatedPurposeModal}}
        <p>
          Before this tool can generate you a statement, you will need to  list the reasons you collect personal information.
        </p>
        <p>
          You're required to have a defined purpose for all the information you collect&mdash;if you can’t tell people why you need the information, it’s better to not collect it.
        </p>
        <p>
          See <a href="https://privacy.org.nz/purpose-for-collection-of-personal-information-principle-one/" target="_blank">Privacy Principle 1</a>
          for more.
        </p>
    {{/modal-message}}

    {{#modal-message showModal=showNotReadyModal}}
        <p> If you collect information you'll need at least one purpose.</p>
    {{/modal-message}}

  </div>

  <div class="pure-u-1-4">
      {{#step-help buttonText="I need a purpose?"}}
              <p>
                You need a <em>purpose</em> related to a function of your business for each piece of information you collect. The information you collect must be necessary for these purposes, and needs to support your business in a clearly defined way. If you don’t actually need the information, it’s better to not collect it.
              </p>

              <p>
                Identifying a clear purpose and sticking to it is the key to getting privacy right. See <a href="https://privacy.org.nz/purpose-for-collection-of-personal-information-principle-one/" target="_blank">Privacy Principle 1</a>
                for more.
              </p>
      {{/step-help}}
  </div>

</div>
